article.description: SE Missouri State 75, South Dakota St 68
article.headline: SE Missouri State 75, South Dakota St 68
article.linkText: SE Missouri State 75, South Dakota St 68
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- David Johnson scored 16 points to lead Southeast Missouri to a 75-68 victory over South Dakota State on Thursday night. Terrick Willoughby added 14 points and Roy Booker had 12 for the Redhawks (2-1). Ben Beran led the Jackrabbits (1-3) with 20 points and Steve Holdren added 14.
